in python calculate the average and standard deviation of a list of numbers
import statistics 
from statistics import mean, stdev 
def compute_statistics(numbers):
    avg = mean(numbers)
    std_dev = stdev(numbers)
    return {"average": round(avg, 2), "standard deviation": round(std_dev, 2)}
# example usage
numbers = [1.0, 2.5, 3.8, 4.2, 5.6]
result = compute_statistics(numbers)
print("Average: {:.2f}".format(result["average"]))
print("Standard deviation: {:.2f}".format(result["standard deviation"]))
